    "recap_headline": "TCU",
    "recap_text": "FORT WORTH\n\u2013 Behind seven shutout innings from\nLance Davis\n, TCU evened the series with a 6-0 win over UCF Saturday night at Lupton Stadium.\nColton Griffin\nand\nLucas Franco\nkeyed the offense, each driving in two runs.\nThe Rundown\nLance Davis\n(1-3) was outstanding in holding league-leading UCF to just two hits and four total base runners over seven innings of work. He never faced more than four batters in an inning and in four innings, he faced the minimum. He finished the night allowing two hits, two walks and striking out five.\nThe offense proved to be opportunistic, taking advantage of their opportunities when they came along. With one out and runners on the corners,\nSawyer Strosnider\nand\nChase Brunson\nexecuted a double steal to get the Frogs on the board, 1-0.\nTCU tacked on an unearned run in the second.\nLucas Franco\nreached on a one-out single. A passed ball and a wild pitch had him standing on third with one out and he scored on a grounder off the bat of\nRob Liddington\nfor a 2-0 lead.\nTwo hit batters and a walk in the fifth had the bases loaded with two outs.\nColton Griffin\nworked a four-pitch walk to give the Frogs a 3-0 lead. Franco followed with a two-run single to give the Frogs some breathing room, 5-0.\nThe Frogs added another insurance run in the seventh, taking advantage of a lead-off walk to Brunson. He was on third with one out and scored on a suicide squeeze off the bat of Griffin to make it 6-0.\nWalter Quinn\nclosed the game with two scoreless frames. He worked around two base runners in the eighth and one in the ninth to secure the shutout victory.\nStat of the Game:\n1 \u2013\nUCF had only one batter reach third base in the game.\nNotes:\n\u2022 TCU registered its first shutout of the season.\n\u2022 TCU scored a first inning run for the 13\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU registered a stolen base in a game for the 17\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU stole multiple bases (4) in a game for the ninth time this season.\n\u2022 TCU scored three of its six runs with two outs.\n\u2022 TCU played flawless defense for the seventh time this season.\n\u2022 TCU turned one double play in the game.\n\u2022 For the ninth time this season, TCU drew more walks (6) than it struck out (4).\n\u2022\nChase Brunson\nrecorded his sixth multi-hit game of the year and the 34\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nColton Griffin\nhas reached safely in 13 straight games.\n\u2022 Griffin posted his second multi-RBI game of the season and the 10\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nLucas Franco\ntallied his fifth career multi-hit game and his fourth career multi-RBI game.\nNext Up:\nWith the win, TCU improves to 13-9 on the season and 2-3 in Big 12 play.\u00a0TCU and UCF will play the rubber match of the series Sunday. First pitch is set for 1 p.m. The game will be televised on ESPN+.",
